OL,6,F"We have worked with our local police
OL,7,Fforces to secure convictions against
OL,8,Fpeople who have attacked our staff and
OL,9,Fcurrent legislation can see such
OL,10,Fperpetrators jailed for up to two
OL,11,Fyears."
OL,13,FSCAS said staff are provided with body
OL,14,Fworn cameras and additional training
OL,15,Fto keep themselves safe as well as a
OL,16,Frange of support should they be the
OL,17,Fvictims of verbal or physical abuse.
OL,19,FBut with record levels of attacks they
OL,20,Fsaid more action is needed at a
OL,21,Fnational level.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/10
